                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">f. 1r-1</locus>
                           <desc>v-131v: Inventory of books in the possession of the church
                              library.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written in a recent hand (in pen and pencil). The ordinal
                              numbers of the books are given in Arabic numerals. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#107ra">f. 107ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#107ra">107ra</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘሐለቃ፡ ገብረ፡ &lt;...&gt;
                              ዘወሐብዎ፡ ለአቡነ፡ &lt;...&gt; ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡
                              ለይኩን፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">[<locus target="#107ra">107ra</locus>]: This book
                              belongs to ḥaläqa Gabra ... who has donated it to ʾabuna ... so that
                              it might be for him the guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. Anyone who
                              stole it it or erased (its text) will be excommunicated by the
                              authority of Peter and Paul.</quote>
                           <note> Part of the donor’s name and the name of the institution to which
                              the Ms. was donated have been erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The scribe(s) did not pay much attention to the ruling
                           lines.
 - <locus target="#0r">0r</locus>, 0v. Crude notes and drawing
                           of a cross.
 - <locus target="#5v">5v</locus>, 39v (in the upper
                           margin): Crude notes.
 - <locus target="#27r">27r</locus> (in the
                           upper and right-hand margins): Crude notes.
 - <locus from="132r" to="132v">132r-132v</locus>: Crude notes, some of them probably
                           listing objects in possession of the church.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings are indicated by the names of the
                              month, written in the upper margin: reading for Tāḫśāś: <locus target="#2r">fol. 2r</locus> reading for Ṭǝrr: <locus target="#26r">fol. 26r</locus> reading for Yakkātit: <locus target="#34r">fol.
                                 34r</locus> reading for Maggābit: <locus target="#41r">fol.
                                 41r</locus> reading for Miyāzyā: <locus target="#50r">fol.
                                 50r</locus> reading for Gǝnbot: <locus target="#57v">fol.
                                 57v</locus> reading for Sane: <locus target="#65r">fol. 65r</locus>
                              reading for Yakkātit: <locus target="#73v">fol. 73v</locus> reading
                              for Ḥamle: <locus target="#74v">fol. 74v</locus> reading for Näḥase:
                                 <locus target="#82r">fol. 82r</locus>. - Crude notes indicating
                              other readings, written in the upper margin: ዘቅዳሜ: <locus target="#77v">fol. 77v</locus> ዘእሁድ: <locus target="#94v">fol.
                                 94v</locus> ዘኪዳነ: ቃል፡ <locus target="#97v">fol. 97v</locus> ዘልደቱ:
                                 <locus target="#123v">fol. 123v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
